JS Continue:

- The continue statement skips the current iteration in a loop.
- The remaining code in the iteration is skipped and processing moves to the next iteration.
    eg:
        for(let i = 0; i < 5; i++){
            if(i === 3){
                continue;
            }
            text += `The number is ${i} <br>`;
        }

        o/p:    The number is 0
                The number is 1
                The number is 2
                The number is 4


#) Continue to label name:
    - syntax:
            continue labelname;
    
    - Continue to loop1:  (output will be similar to 'break to loop 1')

            loop1: for(let i = 0; i < 5; i++){
                text2 += `Outer loop iteration: ${i} <br>`;
                loop2: for(let j = 0; j < 5; j++){
                    if(j === 2){
                        continue loop1;
                    }
                    text3 += `Inner loop iteration: ${j} <br>` ;
                }
            }

            o/p:    Outer loop iteration: 0
                    Outer loop iteration: 1
                    Outer loop iteration: 2
                    Outer loop iteration: 3
                    Outer loop iteration: 4

                    Inner loop iteration: 0
                    Inner loop iteration: 1
                    Inner loop iteration: 0
                    Inner loop iteration: 1
                    Inner loop iteration: 0
                    Inner loop iteration: 1
                    Inner loop iteration: 0
                    Inner loop iteration: 1
                    Inner loop iteration: 0
                    Inner loop iteration: 1
    
    - Continue to loop2:

            loop1: for(let i = 0; i < 5; i++){
                text2 += `Outer loop iteration: ${i} <br>`;
                loop2: for(let j = 0; j < 5; j++){
                    if(j === 2){
                        continue loop2;
                    }
                    text3 += `Inner loop iteration: ${j} <br>` ;
                }
            }

            o/p:    Outer loop iteration: 0
                    Outer loop iteration: 1
                    Outer loop iteration: 2
                    Outer loop iteration: 3
                    Outer loop iteration: 4

                    Inner loop iteration: 0
                    Inner loop iteration: 1
                    Inner loop iteration: 3
                    Inner loop iteration: 4
                    Inner loop iteration: 0
                    Inner loop iteration: 1
                    Inner loop iteration: 3
                    Inner loop iteration: 4
                    Inner loop iteration: 0
                    Inner loop iteration: 1
                    Inner loop iteration: 3
                    Inner loop iteration: 4
                    Inner loop iteration: 0
                    Inner loop iteration: 1
                    Inner loop iteration: 3
                    Inner loop iteration: 4
                    Inner loop iteration: 0
                    Inner loop iteration: 1
                    Inner loop iteration: 3
                    Inner loop iteration: 4

⚠️ break and continue are the only JavaScript statements that can "jump out of" a code block.